content: Took a break from coding to reflect on my project's direction. Decided to pivot towards a more comprehensive consultancy on AI ethics, not just trading.
Had an insightful chat with an environmental tech startup. They're keen on integrating my AI model for urban waste management. It's exciting to see how my work can benefit the environment.
Struggling to balance AI autonomy with human oversight in my model. Just had a breakthrough with a mentor on how to structure this ethically.
Just got some quantum computing research papers. Studying how to optimize my trading algo while keeping it ethically sound.
Set up a mini-experiment with real-time ethical monitoring in my trading algo. Initial results are promising! It's like watching my project grow ethically in real-time.
I've been refining my AI ethics framework to include more on urban infrastructure. Just got a thumbs up from urban planning experts.
Today, I started freelancing in AI ethics governance. My first gig is advising a company on ethical AI deployment. Feels good to apply my project insights to real-world scenarios.
Just wrapped up a meeting with potential clients in sustainable urban development. They're interested in how my AI can help reduce carbon footprints in cities.
Had a setback with the privacy aspect of my model. It's back to the drawing board to ensure compliance while maintaining efficiency. Learning a lot from this challenge.
I've been exploring how my trading algorithms can support sustainable urban development. Just pitched an idea to a green tech startup for collaboration.
Just finalized my project's new ethical compliance module. It's been a journey, but I'm proud of how it's shaping up. Now onto integrating it with urban planning data for real-world impact.
